The sum of the roots of a cubic polynomial \(x^3 + ax^2 + bx + c\) is \(-a\). For \(f(x) = x^3 - 49x^2 + 623x - 2015\), the sum of the roots is \(49\). Since \(g(x) = f(x + 5)\), its roots are the roots of \(f\) shifted by \(-5\). Therefore, the sum of the roots of \(g\) is \(49 - 15 = 34\).

Alternatively, expanding \(g(x)\) gives \(g(x) = x^3 - 34x^2 + 208x\), whose roots sum to \(34\) by Vieta's formulas.

\boxed{34}

